	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">and who knows how optimized the C code would be</div>
<br />
<br />I do, and the answer is "not a whole lot". I ended up writing my own assembly level peephole optimizer since I've used tcc-816 (snes-sdk) quite a lot and the code generated by the compiler simply wasn't good enough IMO.
<br />Of course, the proper approach would be to fix the compiler, but that would be a bigger project.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


